title: Want To Buy:  Range for Night Vision / .50 BMG / Title II / Private Property
postcontent:
I'm not wealthy at all, but with a little bit of saving, mac10/11's have been within my price range. The same thing with a set of PVS-14's for night time shooting. Or with .50 BMG rifles. (Right now my finger is itching to pull the trigger on a set of PVS-14's and class 1 IR laser for night shooting!)

But I've never went ahead with any such purchase. Every range I've been to in the area does not allow full-auto fire, does not allow .50 BMG, and is closed before dark.

When I've asked about it, the consensus seems to be that people who own such stuff must have private property to shoot on.

I thought I would ask here on Armslist. 

Does anyone know of a public place where such shooting is possible? Is there anyone with private property around here who would be willing to allow another shooter on their range, maybe for a fee or something?

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Savage 116 .300WinMag w/ IOR Valdada 3-18x42
postcontent:
Raising money for another project, and I haven't really shot this as much as I thought I would.

This Savage 116 I picked up at Cabela's as one of their exclusive offerings. 

From their site:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Savage® Arms Long-Range Stainless Fluted Barrel Rifle
(SKU 03206552)
Cabela’s-exclusive 24" fluted stainless steel barrel
Adjustable AccuTrigger
AccuStock bedding
Available in magnum chamberings
Cabela’s and Savage partnered to build a long-action rifle loaded with features for long-range hunting precision. Features include: a synthetic AccuStock™; an adjustable, sweet-shooting AccuTrigger™; and, best of all, a 24" stainless steel barrel with the tight-grouping accuracy that’s made Savage rifles famous."
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The rifle has exactly 30 shots down the tube. I don't have any pics of the targets, but groups were under 3/4 MOA using HSM 180gr factory reloads.

The glass is an IOR Valdada 3-18x42 FFP Sniper's Hide Edition GEN 4 with Butler Creek caps sitting in low rings on top of a steel Warne 20MOA mount that's been bedded to the receiver. The glass is perfect, though there may be a ring mark if you undo the rings (don't know as I have no reason to take the scope out of the rings).

It also has a Harris 9-13" notched leg bipod with a pod-loc, a cheek riser, and a Tactical Works tactical bolt handle.

Total outlay was probably around $2400. Asking $1900/obo shipped, and I'll throw in the IOR RDS Edge I got with the glass in a promo. Also, a local deal will include ammo.
